# Junior-Manual-QA-Homework-1
RequSettings/Functions on the “Create View” Page 
●	“Report View Name” → sets Report View displayname for the roles: FirmManager and Advisor.
○	Text box
○	Character limit = 255
○	Validation: once user clicks outside of “Report View Name” textbox, validate displayname character count <= 256
■	If Fails validation, then display red border around text box
●	Radio Icon “Report Type” component with options for Firm Report / Client Report → sets Report View viewcontext
●	Radio Icon “Format” component with options for CSV / PDF/ XLS → sets Report View format
●	Radio Icon “Orientation” component with options for Landscape/Portrait → sets Report View orientation
○	IF ReportView format = PDF, then show Orientation component only for FirmManager.
○	Else hide Orientation component
●	Button: “Create View”
○	“Create View” is greyed out and not clickable unless:
■	displayname is not null
■	viewcontext is not null
■	format is not null
■	IF format = PDF, then orientation is null
○	Upon click, attempts to create and save Report View object
■	Save Validation: upon save, validate that displayname must be unique within firm
●	If Fails validation, then display red border around text box and prevent save
■	Save Validation: upon save, validate that displayname character count <=255
●	If Fails validation, then display red border around text box and display message:
○	Upon successful save by clicking Save button, takes you to Report Builder Page.
